      textEn: [
        "The toys of our childhood were all handmade. Whenever someone crafted something new, it would sweep through the entire class, even the whole school.",
        "For a while, we were all obsessed with fighting bamboo joint figurines.",
        "You’d saw a brush handle into a one-inch piece for the head and torso, drill two holes for arms, saw eight shorter pieces for limbs, and thread them together. You had to saw carefully, or they’d split and all your effort would be wasted.",
        "My mother complained I kept losing brushes, while the old brush seller by the school gate did exceptional business.",
        "The classroom desks were so old their surfaces were scored with gaping cracks like the Yellow River and Yangtze—pencils would drop through.",
        "And now, these cracks were perfect for playing with bamboo joint figurines.",
        "Whoever invented the figurine must have grown up at such desks.",
        "Wedge the string threading nine joints into a crack, pull taut, and the figurine would strike a warrior’s pose—legs apart, arms spread, looking like a bodybuilder.",
        "Alternately loosening and tightening the string made it wave and sway. Two figurines together meant a battle—never tiring, never falling.",
        "Sometimes one’s string got stuck, and the “warrior” looked foolish, belly out, just taking a beating.",
        "Tie a popsicle stick to its hand—Sun Wukong with the Golden Cudgel, dubbed “Little Great Sage.” Impressive!",
        "Two discarded knitting hooks became Dou Erdun’s Tiger Head Double Hooks. “King of the Golden Hooks” carved on its chest. Impressive!",
        "Cut a crescent blade from lead, fashion a serpent spear from wire with red thread, then rack your brains for an even more imposing title.",
        "That battered desk had become a legendary battlefield.",
        "Some classmates tried to outdo everyone by gluing an eraser-carved head and making paper armor. But after a few rounds, the head and armor were knocked flying by its own sword. The opponent declared victory.",
        "In truth, the movements were just random jerking from the string. But it really looked like the real thing.",
        "Black Tiger Rips Out the Heart! Mount Tai Crushes from Above! Two Dragons Fight for the Pearl!",
        "Dong-qiang dong-qiang dong-dong-qiang! Dong-dong-qiang!",
        "During recess, the classroom became an arena, a ring of heads crowding in, stomping and clapping. Often the teacher’s arrival was needed for us to realize class had started.",
        "Even in class, we’d stand textbooks up as screens and resume battle—no sound effects this time.",
        "The classmate behind got so absorbed he craned his neck over our shoulders—caught by the eagle-eyed teacher.",
        "The teacher strode over, swept his hand, and the “screen” collapsed. The two figurines, still locked in combat, were confiscated.",
        "After class, utterly dejected, we crept to the holly bushes beneath the office window, hoping the teacher would toss the items out as usual.",
        "Crouching, eyes wide—nothing. About to leave in frustration, my deskmate was peering through the glass with great interest.",
        "I leaned over. Hey, what was this?",
        "There was the teacher playing with the confiscated figurines, pulling strings inside the drawer, muttering, completely absorbed, oblivious to us peeking.",
        "The expression on his face was exactly the same as ours when lost in play.",
        "My deskmate and I exchanged a grin. Hands empty, hearts full. We tiptoed away.",
        "That little bit of resentment and dejection vanished into thin air."
      ],
