      textEn: [
        "The lamplight gradually shrank, warning that the kerosene was running low; it was not a fine brand either, having long since smoked the glass chimney dim. Firecrackers crackled in the neighborhood, tobacco smoke hung in the air: a drowsy night.",
        "I closed my eyes, leaned back in my chair, resting the hand holding the Chuxue Ji on my knee.",
        "In a half-dream, I saw a good story.",
        "This story was beautiful, elegant, and interesting. Many beautiful people and beautiful things interwove like a sheet of brocade sky, and like ten thousand shooting stars they flew about, simultaneously spreading outward to infinity.",
        "I seemed to recall sitting in a small boat along the Shanyin Road. On both banks: tallow trees, new rice, wildflowers, chickens, dogs, groves and dead trees, thatched cottages, pagodas, temples, farmers and village women, village girls, laundry hanging out to dry, monks, straw capes and hats, sky, clouds, bamboo… all reflected in the clear green river. With each stroke of the oars, each reflection carried shimmering sunlight, together with the duckweed, algae, and fish in the water, all rippling. Every shadow and thing dissolved, swaying, expanding, merging; just as they merged, they contracted again, nearly returning to their original forms. Their edges were jagged as summer clouds, edged with sunlight, emitting a mercury-colored glow. Every river I had ever passed through was just like this.",
        "The story I now saw was the same. Against the blue sky reflected in the water, everything interlaced above it, woven into a single piece, forever vivid, forever unfolding. I could not see its end.",
        "Under a withered willow by the riverbank, a few slender hollyhocks—perhaps planted by a village girl. Red and mottled red flowers floated in the water, suddenly scattering, stretching out like threads of rouge, yet without blurring. Thatched cottages, dogs, pagodas, village girls, clouds… all floated too. Each red flower was elongated into a splashing ribbon of red brocade. The ribbon wove into the dog, the dog into white clouds, the clouds into the village girl… In an instant they contracted again. But the mottled red flower’s shadow had already scattered and stretched, about to weave into the pagoda, the village girl, the dog, the cottage, the clouds.",
        "The story I saw now became clear: beautiful, elegant, interesting, and distinct. Above the blue sky, countless beautiful people and things—I saw them all, knew them all.",
        "I was about to gaze upon them…",
        "Just as I was about to gaze, I startled awake. The brocade sky had crumpled into disorder, as if someone had hurled a great stone into the river, and the waves leaped up, tearing the entire reflection to pieces. Unconsciously I clutched the Chuxue Ji, nearly fallen to the floor. Before my eyes remained a few iridescent fragments.",
        "I truly loved this good story. While the fragments remained, I wanted to recapture it, complete it, preserve it. I tossed the book aside, sat up, and reached for my pen—but where were the fragments? Only the dim lamplight. I was no longer in the little boat.",
        "But I always remember having seen this good story, on a drowsy night…"
      ],
